Update : As per Spring&#39;s [ResponseBodyEmitter][11] Docs, it states that :

&gt; Write the given object to the response.
&gt; 
&gt; If any exception occurs a dispatch is made back to the app server
&gt; where Spring MVC will pass the exception through its exception
&gt; handling mechanism.
&gt; 
&gt; Note: if the send fails with an IOException, you do not need to call
&gt; completeWithError(Throwable) in order to clean up. Instead the Servlet
&gt; container creates a notification that results in a dispatch where
